# MyOccasions Architecture

Laravel REST API — occasions marketplace connecting Clients with Service Providers (halls, restaurants, photographers, etc.).

## Request Flow

```
Route → Controller → Service → Repository → Model
           ↓            ↓
      FormRequest    Resource
```

## Target Folder Structure (use for all new/refactored code)

```
app/Repositories/{ModelName}/Interface/{ModelName}RepositoryInterface.php
app/Repositories/{ModelName}/Implementation/{ModelName}Repository.php
app/Services/{ModelName}/Interface/{ModelName}ServiceInterface.php
app/Services/{ModelName}/Implementation/{ModelName}Service.php
app/Http/Resources/{Entity}/{Entity}Resource.php
app/Http/Requests/{Entity}/{Action}{Entity}Request.php
```

Legacy flat repos/services (interface + impl at same level) → migrate when touched.

## Layer Rules

- **Controller**: HTTP only. Call Service, return Handler + Resource. No Eloquent.
- **Service**: Business logic, transactions, auth checks. Inject Repository interfaces.
- **Repository**: All queries + eager loads. No business rules.
- **Resource**: JSON shape only. No DB calls.
- **Bind** every new interface in `AppServiceProvider`.

## Domain Essentials

- `User` polymorphic → `Client` | `ServiceProvider`
- `OrderStatus`: `under_review` → `accepted` | `rejected`
- Clients see accepted content only
- i18n via `Accept-Language: ar|en`
- Auth guards: `auth:api`, `auth:owner`, `auth.provider.or.owner`

## Adding Features Checklist

Migration → Model → Repository (Interface+Impl) → Service (Interface+Impl) → FormRequest → Resource → Controller → Routes → AppServiceProvider bind
